    "eyebrow": "Concepts",
    "num": "06",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">06</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Concepts</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Cultural Complexity of Texican Identity</h2><ul><li>Texican culture blends Spanish, Mexican, and indigenous influences</li><li>Language, religion, and customs reflect this mixture</li><li>Identity evolved through interaction with Anglo settlers and political change</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican identity is culturally complex, shaped by Spanish colonial heritage, Mexican citizenship, and indigenous influences. This blend created unique traditions and social norms that evolved amid Anglo-American immigration and political upheaval. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> s2 highlights how Catholicism and Spanish language persisted among Texicans even as Anglo settlers introduced Protestantism and English.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Describe how cultural influences combined to form Texican identity.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing Texican culture as monolithic or static over time.</p></div></div>",
