    "num": "07",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">07</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Concepts</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Political and Social Role of Texicans in Early Texas</h2><ul><li>Texicans were key players in Texas's transition from Mexican territory to U.S. statehood</li><li>They experienced shifting loyalties during the Texas Revolution</li><li>Texicans maintained social structures rooted in Hispanic traditions</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans played a significant role in early Texas history, navigating complex political changes and maintaining social customs. Their loyalties during the Texas Revolution were diverse and sometimes conflicted. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s5\">[5]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> s5 documents instances where Texicans supported both Mexican authorities and Texan independence, reflecting divided loyalties.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze how Texican political loyalties influenced their role in Texas history.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming all Texicans uniformly supported either Mexico or Texas independence.</p></div></div>",
