    "num": "15",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">15</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Frontier Challenges</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Environmental and Security Challenges Faced by Texicans</h2><ul><li>Harsh climate with droughts and floods impacted agriculture</li><li>Frequent conflicts with indigenous groups threatened settlements</li><li>Limited infrastructure made travel and communication difficult</li><li>Isolation required self-reliance and community cooperation</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans faced environmental hardships such as unpredictable weather and limited resources. Additionally, frontier security was a constant concern due to conflicts with indigenous peoples and the need for mutual defense among settlers. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> During drought years, Texicans had to ration water and adapt farming practices to survive.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Explain how environmental and security challenges shaped Texican community life.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Underestimating the impact of isolation on Texican resilience.</p></div></div>",
