    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">19</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Practices</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Religious and Festive Life of Texicans</h2><ul><li>Catholicism was central to Texican identity and daily life</li><li>Religious festivals marked the calendar and reinforced community bonds</li><li>Rituals blended Spanish Catholic and indigenous traditions</li><li>Churches served as social and cultural centers</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Religion shaped Texican cultural practices, with Catholic festivals and rituals providing structure and social cohesion. Indigenous influences persisted in some ceremonies, creating a unique cultural blend. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> The feast of Our Lady of Guadalupe was widely celebrated with processions and communal meals.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Discuss how religious festivals reinforced Texican community identity.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming religious practices were purely European without indigenous influence.</p></div></div>",
