    "eyebrow": "Community Resilience",
    "num": "22",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">22</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Community Resilience</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">How Texicans Adapted to Frontier Hardships</h2><ul><li>Developed cooperative labor systems for farming and defense</li><li>Maintained cultural traditions to strengthen identity</li><li>Formed alliances with indigenous groups when possible</li><li>Used local knowledge to manage environmental risks</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans responded to frontier challenges through cooperation, cultural continuity, and strategic alliances, enabling communities to survive and thrive despite hardships. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Communities organized mutual aid groups to build irrigation ditches and protect against raids.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify strategies Texicans used to overcome frontier difficulties.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing Texicans as isolated rather than interconnected and adaptive.</p></div></div>",
