    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">23</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Historical Perspectives</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Primary Source Insights on Texican Daily Life</h2><ul><li>Letters and diaries reveal personal experiences and challenges</li><li>Legal documents show land disputes and governance issues</li><li>Religious records highlight cultural and social practices</li><li>Sources provide nuanced views beyond broad historical narratives</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Primary sources offer detailed evidence of Texican life, illustrating the complexity of their experiences and challenging simplified historical accounts. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A diary entry describes a family’s response to a drought and indigenous raids.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze how primary sources deepen understanding of Texican life.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Relying solely on secondary summaries without engaging primary evidence.</p></div></div>",
