    "eyebrow": "Cultural Identity",
    "num": "25",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">25</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Identity</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Spanish Influences on Texican Culture</h2><ul><li>Spanish colonial heritage shaped language, religion, and law</li><li>Catholicism was central to community life and rituals</li><li>Spanish land grant system influenced settlement patterns</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican culture was deeply rooted in Spanish colonial traditions, especially through language, religion, and legal frameworks. Catholicism played a pivotal role in social cohesion, while Spanish land grants structured early Texican settlements. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Many Texican families maintained Catholic festivals and used Spanish legal documents for land ownership.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify how Spanish colonial practices might have influenced Texican family and community structures.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming Texican culture was purely Mexican or Anglo-American, ignoring Spanish colonial legacies.</p></div></div>",
