    "num": "27",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">27</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Identity</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Indigenous Influences on Texican Culture</h2><ul><li>Indigenous peoples contributed language, food, and customs</li><li>Texicans engaged in trade and intermarriage with native groups</li><li>Indigenous knowledge influenced Texican agriculture and survival</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Indigenous cultures significantly influenced Texican identity through shared customs, intermarriage, and practical knowledge. This interaction enriched Texican culture beyond Spanish and Mexican roots. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican diets incorporated indigenous crops like corn and beans, and some families had indigenous ancestry.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify examples of indigenous cultural contributions to Texican daily life.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring indigenous influence or treating Texican culture as solely European-derived.</p></div></div>",
