    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">30</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Historical Role</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texicans’ Military Roles in the Texas Revolution</h2><ul><li>Texicans fought alongside Anglo settlers against Mexican centralists</li><li>Some Texicans remained loyal to Mexico, creating internal divisions</li><li>Texican militias played key roles in battles like the Siege of Bexar</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">During the Texas Revolution, Texicans were divided; many joined the Texian cause against Mexican centralism, while others remained loyal to Mexico. Texican militias were instrumental in early revolutionary battles. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s14\">[14]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican soldiers fought with Anglo militias during the Siege of Bexar in 1835.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Evaluate the reasons behind Texican support for both sides during the revolution.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Portraying Texicans as a monolithic revolutionary group without internal conflict.</p></div></div>",
