    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">31</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Historical Role</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Experiences During Early Texas Statehood</h2><ul><li>Texicans faced cultural marginalization as Anglo settlers increased</li><li>Legal and political systems shifted toward Anglo-American norms</li><li>Texicans worked to preserve cultural traditions amid change</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">After Texas became a republic and later a U.S. state, Texicans encountered challenges maintaining their cultural identity and political influence as Anglo settlers dominated governance and society. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican communities continued Catholic worship and Spanish language use despite Anglo dominance.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Discuss strategies Texicans used to preserve their culture during early statehood.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming Texicans quickly assimilated or disappeared after Anglo settlement.</p></div></div>",
