    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">37</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Primary Sources</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Texican Letters: Insights into Daily Life</h2><ul><li>Letters reveal family ties, economic activities, and social customs.</li><li>Common themes include farming challenges, community events, and political opinions.</li><li>Language reflects Spanish and Mexican cultural influences.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican letters provide firsthand accounts of everyday experiences, showing how families managed frontier life and maintained cultural traditions. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A letter from a Texican farmer describes crop planting delays due to weather and hopes for a good harvest.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze an excerpt from a Texican letter: What does it reveal about their priorities and concerns?</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming letters only reflect elite perspectives; many letters come from diverse social classes.</p></div></div>",
