    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">38</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Primary Sources</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Diary Entries: Texican Social Structures</h2><ul><li>Diaries reveal family roles, gender expectations, and community interactions.</li><li>Entries often mention religious observances and festivals.</li><li>Social hierarchy and kinship ties are evident in daily routines.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican diaries provide intimate perspectives on social life, showing how individuals navigated family duties and community belonging. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s13\">[13]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A diary entry describes preparations for a local fiesta, emphasizing women’s roles in organizing and cooking.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> From a diary excerpt, identify social roles and community values reflected in the text.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overlooking the importance of religious and cultural events in shaping social cohesion.</p></div></div>",
