    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">46</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Reflection</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Reflecting on Texican Identity Through Primary Sources</h2><ul><li>Consider how primary sources shape our understanding of Texican culture.</li><li>Reflect on the diversity of experiences and viewpoints.</li><li>Acknowledge the limitations and biases in historical documents.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Reflection helps learners critically assess how history is constructed from primary evidence. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s13\">[13]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Noting that some voices are underrepresented in letters and diaries, such as indigenous or lower-class perspectives.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Write a brief reflection on what primary sources reveal and conceal about Texican identity.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Taking primary sources at face value without critical evaluation.</p></div></div>",
