    "num": "47",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">47</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Check Your Understanding</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Quiz: Primary Sources and Texican Life</h2><ul><li>What types of information do Texican letters typically provide?</li><li>How do diaries contribute to understanding social roles?</li><li>What legal traditions influenced Texican land ownership?</li><li>Describe the range of political views found in Texican correspondence.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This quiz checks comprehension of primary source insights into Texican daily life, social structures, and politics. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s13\">[13]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Sample answer: Letters reveal personal and political concerns; diaries show family and religious life; land grants reflect Spanish legal influence; political views vary widely.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Answer the quiz questions based on the primary sources studied.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Confusing the content focus of different source types.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide47\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which of the following best defines the term &#39;Texican&#39; in its historical context?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;An Anglo-American settler in Texas&quot;,&quot;A person of Spanish or Mexican descent living in early Texas&quot;,&quot;A Native American tribe in Texas&quot;,&quot;A modern Texan with no historical ties&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:1,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;Historically, &#39;Texican&#39; refers to people of Spanish or Mexican heritage who lived in Texas before and during early statehood, distinguishing them from Anglo settlers.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Explain how the cultural background of Texicans was shaped by Spanish, Mexican, and indigenous influences.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;The answer should describe the blending of Spanish colonial traditions, Mexican governance and culture, and indigenous practices that together formed a unique Texican identity. It should mention examples such as language, religion, family structures, and customs.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;Texicans developed a unique culture influenced by Spanish colonial laws and Catholicism, Mexican political changes, and indigenous customs, resulting in a blended identity distinct from Anglo settlers.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Texicans had a mixed cultural heritage from Spanish, Mexican, and indigenous sources&quot;,&quot;Their identity combined elements of Spanish colonialism, Mexican rule, and native traditions&quot;,&quot;They were culturally distinct due to influences from all three groups&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
