    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">48</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Application</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Applying Primary Source Analysis to Texican Identity</h2><ul><li>Use primary sources to construct a profile of a typical Texican family.</li><li>Identify cultural influences evident in their daily life and political views.</li><li>Discuss how primary evidence challenges or supports secondary narratives.</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">This application exercise integrates primary source analysis to deepen understanding of Texican identity and history. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s10\">[10]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s11\">[11]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s12\">[12]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s13\">[13]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Combining diary descriptions of family roles with letters expressing political concerns creates a multidimensional Texican profile.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Develop a brief profile of a Texican family using primary source excerpts provided.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Relying solely on secondary sources without engaging primary evidence.</p></div></div>",
