    "eyebrow": "Interactions and Conflicts",
    "num": "51",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">51</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Interactions and Conflicts</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Anglo Settlers and Indigenous Peoples: Conflict and Displacement</h2><ul><li>Anglo settlers often viewed indigenous peoples as obstacles to expansion</li><li>Frequent violent clashes led to indigenous displacement and loss of land</li><li>Settler militias and government policies accelerated indigenous marginalization</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Anglo settlers' expansionist aims frequently resulted in violent conflicts with indigenous peoples, contributing to their displacement and reshaping Texas demographics. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s3\">[3]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Militia campaigns against indigenous tribes were common as settlers sought to secure land for farming and ranching.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Evaluate the impact of settler expansion on indigenous communities in early Texas.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring the role of settler militias and policies in indigenous displacement oversimplifies the causes of conflict.</p></div></div>",
