      "body": "<p><strong>Why this deserves a deeper look.</strong> Anglo settlers' expansionist aims frequently resulted in violent conflicts with indigenous peoples, contributing to their displacement and reshaping Texas demographics.</p><p><strong>Source boundary.</strong> Teach this point from en.wikipedia.org; kids.nationalgeographic.com; thestoryoftexas.com. If a learner asks for a statistic, date, standard, or local procedure that is not in the knowledge base, Bernard and the presenter should mark it as a research gap instead of improvising.</p><h3>What to emphasize</h3><ul><li>Anglo settlers often viewed indigenous peoples as obstacles to expansion</li><li>Frequent violent clashes led to indigenous displacement and loss of land</li><li>Settler militias and government policies accelerated indigenous marginalization</li></ul><h3>Worked example</h3><p>Militia campaigns against indigenous tribes were common as settlers sought to secure land for farming and ranching.</p><h3>Practice and transfer</h3><p>Evaluate the impact of settler expansion on indigenous communities in early Texas.</p><p><strong>Common mistake to prevent.</strong> Ignoring the role of settler militias and policies in indigenous displacement oversimplifies the causes of conflict.</p><p class=\"ref\"><strong>Source anchor:</strong> en.wikipedia.org; kids.nationalgeographic.com; thestoryoftexas.com <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s3\">[3]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p>"
