    "eyebrow": "Interactions and Conflicts",
    "num": "53",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">53</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Interactions and Conflicts</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Post-Revolution Texican Experiences and Challenges</h2><ul><li>Texicans faced marginalization in the new Republic of Texas dominated by Anglo settlers</li><li>Land disputes and legal challenges increased for Texican families</li><li>Cultural assimilation pressures threatened Texican traditions and language</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">After the Texas Revolution, Texicans often struggled to maintain their land, rights, and cultural identity amid Anglo political dominance and changing laws. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican land grants were frequently challenged or ignored by Anglo newcomers, leading to loss of property.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze how political changes after the revolution affected Texican social and economic status.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming Texicans seamlessly integrated into the new Texas society overlooks systemic challenges they faced.</p></div></div>",
