    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">55</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Contested Perspectives</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Divergent Views on Texican Identity</h2><ul><li>Some historians emphasize Texicans as Mexican loyalists preserving Hispanic culture</li><li>Others highlight Texicans as early Texans embracing independence and Anglo influences</li><li>Debates exist over whether Texicans were distinct or assimilated into broader Texan identity</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Historical interpretations of Texican identity vary, reflecting contested views on their cultural and political roles in Texas history. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s9\">[9]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> One view portrays Texicans as defenders of Mexican traditions; another sees them as hybrid actors adapting to Anglo dominance.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Compare these perspectives and decide which is better supported by evidence.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Accepting a single narrative without considering alternative interpretations limits understanding.</p></div></div>",
